      • Shopper

        public Shopper(java.util.List<GroceryInterface> groceries,
               int time)
        Creates a new Shopper that has a unique ID that no previously created Shopper has. The created Shopper's shopping list will be a copy of the list specified.
        Parameters:
        groceries - the shoppers grocery list
        time - the time this Shopper entered the store
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if groceries is null

      • selectLine

        public boolean selectLine(java.util.List<CheckoutLineInterface> lines)
        Given a List of CheckoutLineInterface's, this Shopper may choose to add itself to the line. This method returns true if the Shopper entered a line and false if the shopper did not select a line.
        Parameters:
        lines - the List of CheckoutLineInterface for the store
        Returns:
        whether or not the shopper entered a line
